StoryAsset.name: New Draw First and New Draw Second PostMatch

keyValuePair.Value: Was there anything at all between the teams?
%1s are celebrating going through on away goals. You must be frustrated. There was so little between the two teams. Can you put your finger on why your lads missed out?
We worked so hard but we're out.

We ran and ran. Phenomenal effort from every single player. But it just hasn't gone our way. In games this closely matched, you need a little bit of luck to have things go your way. All I can say is we definitely didn't get the run of the ball here.
I'm proud of the boys despite us going out.

I think every supporter could see the lads gave it everything here. It just wasn't meant to be, perhaps. Games like this are decided on fine margins. I'll look back, analyse, and decide how we can improve.
We had our chance and we passed it up.

I was confident we'd be strong enough to get the win we needed in this second leg. But we made mistakes early on. That put us under pressure and dented our confidence and we ended up chasing the game. You could say we were unlucky, but we can't offer that as an excuse.
How disappointing is it to miss out on the semis?
The tie was always in the balance and you've come out second-best only on away goals. They go through to the semis. Are you left frustrated, or can you still be proud of your team?
It could easily have been us.

We were up against a good side here. The lads worked so hard to keep them at arm's length but it wasn't enough. I don't think we should have any regrets. WE gave it everything. It could so easily have been us in the semi-final, you know.
I'm sorry. Not for me or the players. I'm sorry for the fans.

Football can be very tough to take. We gave as good as we got over the two legs. There really wasn't much between the two teams. I just feel bad for our fans. They were magnificent and deserved to watch us in the semi-finals, that's for sure.
I'm disappointed we couldn't find the goal we needed.

I really thought it would be us going through to the semi-finals. But, when it's tight, you need your star players to make a difference. The opposition were disciplined and made it difficult for us to get on the ball in good areas. We just couldn't get the goal we needed. Because of that, we're out.
You've gone out. Was there something missing from your game today?
%1s were very well-organised and, of course, they have some excellent players. But with a semi-final place at stake, are you disappointed your team couldn't find something extra today?
It's about fine margins at this level.

At this stage of the competition, it's very fine margins which decide games. I thought the boys gave everything. I just wish we'd been clever enough - or lucky enough - to create the one clear-cut chance which could have swung things our way.
We'll have to get over it.
We can't feel sorry for ourselves now. It was close and I wish we could have given our fans something to celebrate. But we've got to find a positive state of mind for the games we've got coming up.
We missed our chance, for sure.

We were desperate to reach the semis and maybe we tried too hard. I think we tried to play careful, intricate football in the wrong areas of the pitch and we paid the price for losing the ball. We'll look back and know that we've missed a great chance here.
Can you come back from this disappointment?

I know everyone at the club was hoping to see %1s in the %2s Final. It took away goals to separate the teams over the two legs, but defeat must be a big blow to your players' hopes. Can they recover from this?
The lads left everything out there.

They're professional players and they'll recover, that's for sure. But I think this defeat will haunt one or two of the older players. They put so much into the two games and probably deserved a place in the Final. Is that their last chance gone?
What doesn't kill you makes you stronger, right?
We've done so well to get this far in the competition. Of course it's a blow not to make it to the Final. But I hope we now believe we're good enough to come back even stronger next season.
We didn't dare enough today.

I know how badly our fans wanted to see us reach the %1s Final, but we probably lacked a bit of courage and a bit of self-belief today. Our opponents took the risks you need to take in tight games to make the difference. They dared. We didn't.

I know how badly our fans wanted to see us reach the %1s Final, but we probably lacked a bit of courage and a bit of self-belief today. Our opponents took the risks you need to take in tight games to make the difference. They dared. We didn't.
It was a very nervy finish. Did your boys deserve to go through?
That was a very closely-fought tie. You've just managed to scrape through on away goals. Are you happy with how the team performed or are you looking at how you can improve?
Let's kick on now!
It's great to have qualified. Yes, it was close, but we have to make the most of this opportunity now. I know we can still improve. I want to see us use this result as motivation moving forward.
We've achieved nothing yet.
We're happy to be through, but the fact that it came down to away goals to decide it proves we have to remain humble. As far as I'm concerned, we still have a lot of work to do.
Every tackle counts!

I was really pleased with how we've competed over these two games. Getting tackles in, tracking runners, fighting for everything. Those were the things that kept us in it when we were under pressure and we had enough composure to make sure we got the draw today. All the hard work paid off.
That must have been nerve-wracking! How pleased are you to reach the semis?
That was a very close-run thing. You were up against a very good team in these two games, though. Surely your boys can be proud of claiming a place in the semi-final?
It's all about keeping your nerve.

That was a very hard-fought game and us going through on away goals tells you it could have gone either way. If we're going to reach the Final now, we'll need that willingness to dig in and battle. We'll need to keep our heads from the first minute to the last.
Let's get used to winning!

It doesn't matter how it's achieved. It's about getting through. Good results build confidence. I want to see more positive performances now to put us in the right frame of mind ahead of the semi-final.
We've got leaders in the team.
We've got leaders in the team.

Team spirit is really good in our dressing room. We've got some natural leaders in this squad and you can see how important they are to us. We know we can be resilient and can count on each other when it matters. That gives the lads the confidence to find a way through, even in the tightest situations.

Team spirit is really good in our dressing room. We've got some natural leaders in this squad and you can see how important they are to us. We know we can be resilient and can count on each other when it matters. That gives the lads the confidence to find a way through, even in the tightest situations.
So, through on away goals. Are your boys ready to take the next step?
You're through on away goals and that's the important thing. But were you nervous today? Are your lads ready to the next step up from here in the competition?
We matched their intensity.

The important thing was we always stayed in both legs of the tie. We knew we'd have to match them for desire and we did that. Now we can add quality, I hope, and work on finding a bit more craft and fluency when we've got the ball. We'll stick together and see what happens.
This was an essential target.
I was always confident we'd find a way through. Qualifying is very important, not just for me and the players, but for the whole club. I'm glad we've made it.
Maybe the lads have a point to prove.

I'm pleased with the effort and desire right from everyone. Over these two legs, we've deserved to qualify. I hope we've silenced a few doubters, too. I know there are people who don't fancy this team's prospects much. The lads are in the mood to prove those people wrong.
Where does reaching this final rank amongst your achievements?

You've enjoyed your share of good times in the past, of course, but you must be very pleased to be into the %2s Final after today. How much could this kind of success mean to a club like %1s going forward?
Let's keep this run going!

It was tight but I think we deserved it over the two legs. Well done to the whole team. They're proud to represent the club and, better still, they're in great form right. I can't wait to start getting them ready for the Final now!
We have to go there and win now!

Well done to the lads for getting us through a really difficult semi-final. We've got a lot of football to play in the next few weeks. Then we can focus on the Final. We won't be going there just to come away as runners-up, I promise!
Fantastic commitment from the boys.

I think over these two games you've seen what we're all about. We've been dogged, brave, intelligent and proud to wear the %1s shirt. Those are all big qualities I look for from my players. This team deserves to be successful now.
